    "recap_headline": "Quinnipiac University",
    "recap_text": "Hamden, Conn. \u2013\nThe Quinnipiac Bobcats took the series finale, 10-2, from the Sacred Heart Pioneers, as they avoided the sweep in their first MAAC series of the season. With the win, the Bobcats improved to 5-11 overall and 1-2 in conference play.\nSCORE\nQuinnipiac 10, Sacred Heart 2\nRECORDS\nQuinnipiac (5-11, 1-2 MAAC) | Sacred Heart (4-12, 3-3 MAAC)\nWinning Pitcher \u2013\nAndrew Rubayo\n(1-0)\nLosing Pitcher \u2013\u00a0Anakin Underhill (0-2)\nHOW IT HAPPENED\nAndrew Rubayo\nset the Pioneers down in order to start the contest, bringing the Bobcats up to the plate with a 0-0 score. Quinnipiac took full advantage of the shutdown inning, scoring seven in their half of the first to open a seven-run lead.\nCole Constable\ngot the scoring started as he flew out to center, bringing home\nCaden Williamson\nwith the game's first run. With two outs in the inning,\nJames Marino\nput the ball in play, and\nPeyton Vancas\nbeat the play at second to extend the inning as\nAlex Irizarry\nscored the second run of the inning.\nMatt Park\n, the next batter, stood in the box and got hit with the pitch to bring home the third run of the inning. With the bases loaded and two outs,\nBrendan Edvardsen\nunloaded on a pitch, sending it over the left field wall for a grand slam to give the Bobcats a seven-run first inning.\nThe score would remain 7-0 until the fourth inning, when Ronan Donohue singled home Jacob Schmutz to cut the Sacred Heart deficit to six.\nQuinnipiac got that run back in the bottom half of the sixth inning as\nCole Constable\nsingled to the shortstop, scoring\nCaden Williamson\nto make it 8-1, Bobcats.\nAfter the Pioneers made it an 8-2 game in the top half of the seventh, the Bobcats added on two more runs to make it a 10-2 ballgame.\nMatt Park\ndoubled down the right field line, scoring\nJames Marino\nfrom first base. Park would later come in to score on a\nCaden Williamson\ngroundout for QU's tenth run of the contest.\nJ.C. Franconere\nand\nMatt Alduino\npitched the final two innings for the Bobcats, shutting the door and helping the Bobcats earn their first MAAC win of the season.\nNEWS AND NOTES\nSeven different Bobcats recorded hits in the series finale against the Pioneers.\nCaden Williamson\nwas the lone Bobcat to record multiple hits in the effort, finishing the game with two base hits.\nBrendan Edvardsen\npicked up his first home run as a Bobcat with his first-inning grand slam.\nEdvardsen led the Bobcats with four RBIs in the win, pushing his season total to five.\nMatt Park\nand\nCole Constable\neach drove in two runs in the win. Park now has seven RBIs on the season, while Constable has four.\nAndrew Rubayo\nhad a phenomenal start on the mound, going 7.0 innings, allowing just two earned runs, and striking out five.\nJ.C. Franconere\nand\nMatt Alduino\ncombined for the final six outs, each not allowing a base runner in their appearances.\nON DECK\nThe Bobcats will take on the Central Connecticut State Blue Devils on Tuesday, March 17\nth\n, at 3 PM in New Britain, Connecticut."
